# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Before deploying with this .env file:
#
# 1. SECURITY - Change ALL placeholder values:
#    - SECRET_KEY (generate new one with: python manage.py shell -c "from django.core.management.utils import get_random_secret_key; print(get_random_secret_key())")
#    - DB_PASSWORD (use strong password, e.g., from: openssl rand -base64 32)
#    - REDIS_PASSWORD (use strong password, e.g., from: openssl rand -base64 32)
#    - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID & SECRET (if using OAuth)
#
# 2. PROJECT STRUCTURE:
#    - Project path: /var/www/html/lms
#    - Docker containers run within this directory
#    - Nginx reverse proxy configured to route lms.khaz.app → Docker containers
#
# 3. SSL/HTTPS:
#    - SSL certificates configured on nginx
#    - DEBUG=False enforces HTTPS redirects
#    - Let's Encrypt certificates at: /etc/letsencrypt/live/lms.khaz.app/
#
# 4. DATABASE & REDIS:
#    - Both services run as Docker containers
#    - Accessible via hostname (postgres, redis) within Docker network
#    - First deployment auto-runs migrations

#
# 4. VERIFICATION:
#    - Test: curl https://lms.khaz.app/api/v1/health/
#    - Admin: https://lms.khaz.app/admin/
#    - Verify no DEBUG errors exposed
#
# USAGE:
#   Copy this file to .env on staging server:
#   $ cp .env.staging .env
#   $ docker-compose down && docker-compose up -d
